														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4031051">
									

<p>My personal favorite is getting to him just after he was rejected by the Academy in 1907. Instead of killing him, I would get him the best private lessons by the best Jewish art teachers. He would gradually be coached into painting sentimental kitsch depictions of traditional Austrian Jewish life, which would become fashionable among bourgeois Austrian Jewish families.</p>
<p>After a few decades of commercial success, he would die, popular and prosperous, and a generation of Jews would have grown up with 'Hitler' meaning 'those chocolate box pictures Bubbe and Zayde had in the parlor'.</p>

